# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets reads this file (copied into web/out by the
# Next export).

# Security headers on EVERY response (different header names from the Cache-Control
# rules below, so they layer, not conflict): the app is never meant to be iframed
# (anti-clickjacking), browsers must not MIME-sniff, and referrers stay origin-only.
# A full Content-Security-Policy is deliberately omitted — it needs per-app testing
# against the SPA's inline + CDN needs; these three are safe blanket defaults.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

# Content-hashed files under /_next/static/** can never change under the same name,
# so cache them forever — the browser never re-validates them on repeat loads.
# Everything else keeps the safe default (revalidated).
/_next/static/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# The HTML shell, by contrast, must never be reused stale: it names the current
# build's hashed chunks, so an old shell would load a deploy that no longer
# exists. Force a revalidation on every load (the file is tiny). This makes the
# self-heal in version-watch.tsx the belt to this braces — both ends covered.
/*.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
